	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>You hold a forked twig in the air, repeating the name of the object you're looking for. With a few hand gestures, the twig hones in on the object you're looking for, bending and pulling your arm gently in the direction of the object.</em></p><p><strong>Utility Spell</strong></p><ul><li><p>Describe and name an object that you are familiar with: either a specific object (my brother's longsword) or the nearest object of a given type (the nearest rope). Your chosen object must be one you have touched or seen before. You don't need line of sight to the target.</p></li><li><p>You sense the closest object that meets the requirements that you state.</p></li><li><p>If the object is in motion, you know the direction of its movement.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Upcasting:</strong> Range increases by 500 feet for each spell level above 2nd.</p><p><em>This spell can't locate an object if any thickness of lead, even a thin sheet, blocks a direct path between you and the object.</em></p>",
